    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-09-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-09-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="138"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d138">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">561.333D3/9–1247: Airgram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Certain
                            <gloss type="to">Diplomatic Representatives in the American
                            Republics</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="6" xml:id="d138fn1">At Rio de Janeiro, Bogotá, Tegucigalpa, Mexico
                        City, Guatemala, Caracas, Lima, Habana, Port-au-Prince, San José Ciudad
                        Trujillo, Managua, Quito, and San Salvador.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-09-12">September 12,
                            1947</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>On September 11, 1947, the Inter-American Coffee Board passed a motion
                    recommending the continuation of the Inter-American Coffee <pb facs="0176"
                        n="160" xml:id="pg_160"/> Agreement for one year beginning October 1,
                        1947.<note n="7" xml:id="d138fn2">Department of State Treaties and Other
                        International Acts Series No. 1768; 62 Stat. (pt. 2) 1658.</note> Protocol
                    for continuation is the same as Enclosure No. 3 to Instruction to United States
                    Delegate to the Inter-American Coffee Board<note n="8" xml:id="d138fn3">Dated
                        August 4, not printed.</note> with minor changes. Copies of this instruction
                    were sent by transmittal slips in August to Embassies receiving this
                    airgram.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
